<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - FLYWHEEL REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FLYWHEEL REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check flywheel housing bore concentricity and flywheel housing face runout, as described
                    under
                    <hotlnk document="e415_134.xml" xrefid="hl4150702">"Rear Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve
                        Installation"</hotlnk>. See
                    <emph type="bold">Figures
                        <hotlnk document="e415_134.xml" xrefid="ef4150716">7.16</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk document="e415_134.xml" xrefid="ef4150717">7.17</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the flywheel and ring gear assembly as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the two guide studs on the crankshaft flange and slide the flywheel onto the
                        guide studs.
                        <emph type="bold"></emph>
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Be sure the flywheel bolt holes are in line with their mating bolt holes in the
                                crankshaft flange.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install six of the eight mounting bolts. Remove the guide studs and install the two
                        remaining bolts. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150722">7.22</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the flywheel mounting bolts to specified torque. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150721">7.21</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef4150721" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12157" filename="../figcg1/CG12157.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.21. Tighten to Specified Torque.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150722" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12158" filename="../figcg1/CG12158.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.22. Install Flywheel with the Aid of Guide Studs.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Engines equipped with either the AT-540/545 or MT-640/643/653 transmission must have
                                the flywheel installed in conjunction with the parts specified in Figures
                                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150723">7.23</hotlnk>
                                and
                                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150724">7.24</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                    <figure id="ef4150723" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12159" filename="../figcg1/CG12159.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.23. Flywheel Installation for Vehicles with AT-540/545 Transmission.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150724" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12160" filename="../figcg1/CG12160.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.24. Flywheel Installation for Vehicles with MT-640/643/653 Transmission .
                        </caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
